  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sahel Capital - FAFIN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigeria continues to rely on imported food goods in many sectors because of challenges such as fragmented supply chains and outdated farming practices that reduce the competitiveness of local products. FAFIN is an Impact Fund managed by Sahel Capital focussed on making investments in the SME value chain that smallholder farmers rely on to reach Nigerian consumers, this includes areas such as the processing of locally produced goods, storage and packaging.</narrative>
  </description>
